(175, 665, 'The library of the Faculty of Agriculture and Food sciences was reestablished in 1996 and has now a collection of 7.400 volumes from the field of biotechnical sciences which are included in the education program of the Faculty: agronomy, food technology, agro economics and animal production. The library is intended for students, university teachers and teaching assistants, as well as all other interested parties from industry, education and scientific research institutions.', NULL, NULL),
