(191, 681, 'The center generates, develops and transfers technologies and scientific-technical bases of economic and environmental sustainability, within the fields of Reproduction, Genetics and Animal Biotechnology, which enable and / or contribute to the preservation of animal genetic resources and knowledge to increased milk and meat production of efficient, sustainable and increasingly.', NULL, NULL),
(192, 682, 'The institution conducts research to provide scientific and technical basis of production systems on grain varieties of rice, beans, soybeans, sorghum, maize, sesame, vignas, groundnut and chickpea taking into account the needs of the individual and collective farmers of the country, is responsible for the preservation, expansion and characterization of plant genetic resources of the different varieties of grains investigated.', NULL, NULL),
(193, 683, 'The Research Institute for Tropical Fruit is a Research-Development Institute, which has among its fundamental scientific research activities, the provision of scientific and technological services, teaching and production of key inputs for agro fruit.', NULL, NULL),
(194, 684, 'INCA, located in San Jose de las Lajas, Havana Province, was established in 1970, in response to state policy development to research across the country, as research and postgraduate education of the agricultural industry and to extend their results to the productive practice and training to producers. It is a unit of Science and Technology of the Ministry of Higher Education of the Republic of Cuba. At present the institution''s mission: To generate and transfer knowledge updated, comprehensive technologies and new products of biotechnology, plant science and sustainable systems to efficiently raise food production.', NULL, NULL),
(195, 685, 'The Swine Research Institute (IIP), founded in 1972, is listed as rector of Science and Technology in pig farming in Cuba. Reporting to the Group of Pig Production (GRUPOR), Ministry of Agriculture (MINAGRI) develops experimental research, aimed at responding to specific aspects of pig production, extended to countries with the same weather conditions, protecting and preserving the ecological environment . Research has included the areas of genetics, reproduction and nutrition of pigs, as well as facility design and mechanization of the laborious processes, deepening organizational aspects of pig units and treatment of waste .', NULL, NULL),
