nt: inherit; font-weight: bold; line-height: inherit; float: left; display: inline; clear: left;">Software used:&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="field-items" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; float: left; display: inline;">\r\n<div class="field-item even" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 5px !important; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;"><a href="http://ring.ciard.net/category/software/locally-produced-solution" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" style="color: rgb(29, 105, 47); margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: none;" typeof="skos:Concept">Locally produced solution</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', ''),
(310, 800, '', '', ''),
(311, 801, '<p>citaREA is the institutional repository of the Center for Research and Food Technology of Aragon (CITA), public organization of research under the Ministry of Industry and Innovation of the Government of Aragon.</p>', '', ''),
(312, 802, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Chinese Agricultural Sci-tech Documents Database (CASDD), as agricultural bibliographic/abstracts database in China developed by the Agricultural Information Institute（AII） of CAAS (Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences), has the largest number of records and the longest time span of documents.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;It relies on the rich library resources of the AII, covering literature from more than 1000 titles of Chinese agricultural academic journals, proceedings, and other materials, in the fields of agronomy, horticulture, plant protection, soil sciences, animal husbandry, veterinary, agricultural engineering, agricultural products processing, agricultural economic and so on. It is the most comprehensive, reliable and accessible information resources of agricultural science and technology information from research institutions, education and related departments. The database provides searching, consulting, and reference services by phone, mail, document delivery and all kinds of services.&nbsp;</div>', '', ''),
(313, 803, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The AVANO database and search engine (maintained by Ifremer) harvests almost all sources in the areas of oceanography, marine sciences, fisheries &amp; aquaculture. This database and its site do not exist any longer and all the data is currently accessible from the AGRIS portal.</span></p>', 'AV', '0'),
(314, 804, '<p>SciELO The Scientific Library - SciELO Chile, is an electronic library that includes a selected collection of Chilean scientific journals in all areas of knowledge. This regional project is being developed in Chile by the National Commission for Scientific and Technological Research (CONICYT). SciELO The Scientific Library - SciELO Chile, is an electronic library that includes a selected collection of Chilean scientific journals in all areas of knowledge. This regional project is being developed in Chile by the National Commission for Scientific and Technological Research (CONICYT).</p>', 'CL', 'A'),
(315, 805, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">SciELO Colombia is an electronic library covering a select collection of scientific Colombian journals from all areas of knowledge.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;SciELO Colombia has a National Consultative Committee consisting of Colciencias (Instituto Colombiano para el Desarrollo de la Ciencia y la Tecnolog&iacute;a &ldquo;Francisco Jos&eacute; de Caldas&rdquo;), the Pan-American Health Organisation (Colombia), the Universidad Nacional de Colombia and the editors&#39; representatives.</p>\r\n</div>', 'CO', 'A'),
(316, 806, '<p>Cuba SciELO is an electronic library that includes a selected collection of Cuban scientific journals in all areas of knowledge. Powered by Health Telematic Network Cuba (INFOMED) in collaboration with the Latin American and Caribbean Center on Health Sciences in Brazil (NLM), is part of a regional project (http://www.scielo . org).</p>', 'CU', 'Z'),
(317, 807, '', '', ''),
(318, 808, '', '', NULL),
(319, 809, '', '', NULL),
(320, 810, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Scientific Electronic Library Online - SciELO is an electronic library covering a selected collection of Brazilian scientific journals.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;The library is an integral part of a project being developed by FAPESP - Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o de Amparo &agrave; Pesquisa do Estado de S&atilde;o Paulo, in partnership with BIREME - the Latin American and Caribbean Center on Health Sciences Information. Since 2002, the Project is also supported by CNPq - Conselho Nacional de Desenvolvimento Cient&iacute;fico e Tecnol&oacute;gico. The Project envisages the development of a common methodology for the preparation, storage, dissemination and evaluation of scientific literature in electronic format. As the project develops, new journal titles are being added in the library collection.</div>', 'XS', '0'),
(321, 811, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">SciELO Scientific Electronic Library Online es una biblioteca electr&oacute;nica que conforma una red iberoamericana de colecciones de revistas cient&iacute;ficas en texto completo y con acceso abierto, libre y gratuito.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;&nbsp; En Argentina este proyecto cooperativo regional forma parte de las pol&iacute;ticas cient&iacute;ficas del Consejo Nacional de Investigaciones Cient&iacute;ficas y T&eacute;cnicas (CONICET) y se gestiona a trav&eacute;s del Centro Argentino de Informaci&oacute;n Cient&iacute;fica y Tecnol&oacute;gica (CAICYT), organismo dependiente del CONICET. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'AR', 'A'),
(322, 812, '', '', NULL),
(323, 813, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Albanian Journal of Agricultural Sciences (AJAS) is an International official journal of the Agricultural University of Tirana, (Universiteti Bujq&euml;sor i Tiran&euml;s, UBT) Albania. AJAS is an open-access, peer reviewed journal, that considers original articles, reviews and short communications of high scientific standard in the full spectrum of biological and agricultural sciences.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'AL', '1'),
(324, 814, '<p>The mission of the Center for Agricultural Documentation and Information SAGPyA is to provide access to information resources of the agricultural sector to contribute to the research , extension and teaching of its user community . It also seeks to protect and preserve the bibliographical and historical collection , integrating its services and products to the policy established by the agency . The objectives are : To support research, extension , teaching and application information referred agricultural area . Promote the circulation of information . Strengthen research . Coordinate sharing of information found in libraries and documentation centers in the country. Gather, select, process and disseminate bibliographic information specialist . Design strategies to generate projects, services and information products. Promote training in the areas of their responsibility for information units that require it . Coordinate activities to facilitate access to input bibliographic information.</p>', 'AR', '0'),
(325, 815, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Armenian State Agrarian University is the only higher educational institution that trains and prepares specialists for agrarian sphere. ASAU has passed a glorious scientific and educational road, and the University is proud of its graduates who serve for the welfare and prosperity of our state.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Issues concerning the improvement and development of higher education, as well as the quality and utility of research works have always been a priority for the University authority and the personnel. Due to already formed traditions and achieved accomplishments, the University is considered to be one of the leading and outstanding educational institutions in our country.</div>', 'AM', '0'),
(326, 816, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Belarus Agricultural Library (BelAL) is the national information centre for agriculture, food and forestry. The Library was created by the decree of the Council of Ministers of Belarus in 1960. Now the Library is a part of the National Academy of Sciences of Belarus.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Mission of the Library is to provide free access to the agricultural international and national information resources.&nbsp;</div>', 'BY', '0'),
(327, 817, '<p>The library of the Faculty of Agriculture and Food sciences was reestablished in 1996 and has now a collection of 7.400 volumes from the field of biotechnical sciences which are included in the education program of the Faculty: agronomy, food technology, agro economics and animal production. The library is intended for students, university teachers and teaching assistants, as well as all other interested parties from industry, education and scientific research institutions.</p>', 'BA', '0'),
(328, 818, '<p>The journal aims to publish full articles, preliminary notes and review articles in the areas of veterinary medicine, animal husbandry and allied sciences, established by national and / or foreign, provided that meet the editorial standards experts.</p>', 'BR', '9'),
(329, 819, '<p>The National Agricultural Library (Binagri), the Ministry of Agriculture, you can access nearly 400 thousand volumes related to agriculture. Are books, magazines, videos, CD-ROMs and laws dating from the time of Brazil Empire to the present day, transforming Binagri in one of the most comprehensive in the industry in Latin America.</p>', 'BR', '0'),
(330, 820, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Agrarian Journal intended for the publication of articles, scientific papers and technical notes relating to the development of the activity of Agricultural Sciences (Agronomy, Forest Sciences, Agricultural Engineering, Veterinary Medicine, Food Science and Technology, Economics and Administration Agribusiness and Animal Science ).</span></p>', 'BR', '4'),
(331, 821, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Brazilian Journal of Agricultural Sciences is a journal of popular science published by the Federal Rural University of Pernambuco (UFRPE) and has a mission to raise the knowledge produced by the scientific community in the field of Agricultural Sciences. The journal aims to publish original and previously unpublished articles, drawn up in Portuguese, English or Spanish in the areas of Agriculture, Agricultural Engineering, Veterinary Medicine, Forestry and Forestry, Fishery and Fishing Engineering and Animal Husbandry Resources.</span></p>', 'BR', '6'),
(332, 822, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Brazilian Agricultural Research Corporation&#39;s mission is to provide feasible solutions for the sustainable development of Brazilian agribusiness through knowledge and technology generation and transfer.</span></p>', 'BR', '1'),
(333, 823, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Brazilian Journal of Maize and Sorghum is published every four months (April, August, December) of the Association of Corn and Sorghum (ABMS). Aims to publish original research papers from all areas related to crops of maize, sorghum and related species that are significant to the development of agricultural science and agribusiness supply chains related to the species mentioned. Submitted papers must be unpublished, simultaneous presentation being banned in another journal.</span></p>', 'BR', '7'),
(334, 824, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Comunicata Scientiae is a periodical published in annual volumes of four issues (March, June, September and December), edited by the Campus &quot;Professor. Cinobelina Elvas &quot;, Federal University of Piau&iacute; with the aim of publishing articles, scientific notes and literature reviews (at the invitation of the editorial board) that have significant importance to the Agricultural and Environmental Sciences in Portuguese, Spanish or, preferably, in English</span></p>', 'BR', '2'),
(335, 825, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Brazilian Journal of Animal Health and Production (RBSPA) is an e-journal for the publication of scientific papers and review articles under the Animal Health and Production. The RBSPA is published by the Federal University of Bahia / School of Veterinary Medicine and enables its readers the free and full access to articles published in it. Aims to provide the scientific community publications high level, providing results of relevant research in the areas of animal health and production, preventive veterinary medicine and public health, technology and inspection of products of animal origin bioethics, human-animal relationships and environment- related areas.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'BR', '5'),
(336, 826, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Institute of Agricultural Economics (IAE) is a public research organization recently celebrating its 70th anniversary. Since 2000 the IAE is one of the main institutes within the National Centre for Agricultural Sciences, and the only one specialized in agrarian and rural economics research in Bulgaria.</span></p>', 'BG', '0'),
(337, 827, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The International Academy of Ecology and Environmental Sciences (IAEES) is a nonprofit and registered international organization.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;It devotes to promote global ecology and environmental sciences and protect global ecological environments, by publishing scientific publications, conducting research activities, launching environmental programs, disseminating knowledge and technologies, sponsoring conferences, and providing information and discussion spaces, etc.</div>', 'CN', '2'),
(338, 828, '<p><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, 微软雅黑; font-size: 14px; line-height: 30px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 240);">The Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences (CAAS) is a national, integrative agricultural scientific research organization with responsibility for carrying out both basic and applied research, as well as research into new technologies impacting agriculture. CAAS is dedicated to overcoming a broad range of challenges impacting agricultural development and support of the local rural economy. Importantly, CAAS promotes sustainable agriculture within and outside China, extending its reach through technology exchange and cooperative research agreements with agricultural research institutions/universities domestically and internationally. and global non-governmental organizations.</span></p>', 'CN', '0'),
(339, 829, '', 'CO', 'U'),
(340, 830, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Oil palm growers have one of the most dynamic industrial associations in the Colombian agricultural sector: the National Federation of Oil Palm Growers, Fedepalma. Its activities have been decisive in securing a solid position for the agribusiness in this country.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Since it started working in 1962, Fedepalma has promoted all kinds of initiatives to increase the competitiveness of the sector, prioritizing activities which producers or others would not be able to undertake efficiently on their own. Until the 1980&#39;s Fedepalma concentrated much of its efforts on seeking agreements with successive governments regarding the conditions necessary to encourage oil palm production and protect the marketing of its products. In the 1990&#39;s,the expansion and consolidation of the industry required the Federation to promote measures to ensure that the production of palm oil would be more competitive and that the conditions of sales at home and abroad would be more defined. As a result of those efforts, the industry today has a strong infrastructure which includes bodies engaged in research, marketing and oil palm development. The Information Center gathers documents and publications related to the oil palm industry that have been written both in Colombia and all over the world. &nbsp;</div>', 'CO', 'F'),
(341, 831, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Colombian Agricultural Research Corporation, CORPOICA, is a decentralized public entity for services with private regime, responsible for generating scientific knowledge and technological solutions through research, innovation, technology transfer and training of researchers, for the benefit of the agricultural sector Colombian. CORPOICA has a team of over 270 researchers from different disciplines of knowledge, located in seven research centers and eight experimental stations in different regions.</span></p>', 'CO', '0'),
(342, 832, '', 'QT', '0'),
(343, 833, '<p>The center generates, develops and transfers technologies and scientific-technical bases of economic and environmental sustainability, within the fields of Reproduction, Genetics and Animal Biotechnology, which enable and / or contribute to the preservation of animal genetic resources and knowledge to increased milk and meat production of efficient, sustainable and increasingly.</p>', 'CU', 'B');
INSERT INTO `civicrm_value_description_of_collections_29` (`id`, `entity_id`, `description_57`, `agris_country_center_code_64`, `agris_center_code_65`) VALUES
(344, 834, '<p>The institution conducts research to provide scientific and technical basis of production systems on grain varieties of rice, beans, soybeans, sorghum, maize, sesame, vignas, groundnut and chickpea taking into account the needs of the individual and collective farmers of the country, is responsible for the preservation, expansion and characterization of plant genetic resources of the different varieties of grains investigated.</p>', 'CU', '3'),
(345, 835, '<p>The Research Institute for Tropical Fruit is a Research-Development Institute, which has among its fundamental scientific research activities, the provision of scientific and technological services, teaching and production of key inputs for agro fruit.</p>', 'CU', '9'),
(346, 836, '<p>INCA, located in San Jose de las Lajas, Havana Province, was established in 1970, in response to state policy development to research across the country, as research and postgraduate education of the agricultural industry and to extend their results to the productive practice and training to producers. It is a unit of Science and Technology of the Ministry of Higher Education of the Republic of Cuba. At present the institution&#39;s mission: To generate and transfer knowledge updated, comprehensive technologies and new products of biotechnology, plant science and sustainable systems to efficiently raise food production.</p>', 'CU', '4'),
(347, 837, '<p>The Swine Research Institute (IIP), founded in 1972, is listed as rector of Science and Technology in pig farming in Cuba. Reporting to the Group of Pig Production (GRUPOR), Ministry of Agriculture (MINAGRI) develops experimental research, aimed at responding to specific aspects of pig production, extended to countries with the same weather conditions, protecting and preserving the ecological environment . Research has included the areas of genetics, reproduction and nutrition of pigs, as well as facility design and mechanization of the laborious processes, deepening organizational aspects of pig units and treatment of waste .</p>', 'CU', 'Y'),
(348, 838, '', 'CU', '0'),
(349, 839, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Research Institute of Plant Protection (INISAV), with over 20 years providing results to Cuban agriculture is the scientific-technical and methodological support of the State Plant Protection Service, mainly in the plant diagnosis, introduction and media production biological, implementation of programs Integrated Pest Management and monitoring of quality and pesticide residues. They are benefited farmers results associated to the different forms and types of agricultural production.</span></p>', 'CU', '1'),
(350, 840, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The IIA with a team of highly qualified specialists and appropriate for the development of agriculture in tropical regions facilities. It has two research stations with more than 30 buildings, laboratories for the diagnosis and prevention of poultry diseases, for quick and accurate assessment of the nutritional value of unconventional foods, selection and improvement of clean lines and lines forming more rustic and the application of new technologies hosting, rearing and artificial incubation.</span></p>', 'CU', '7'),
(351, 841, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Forest Research Institute is the institution responsible for contributing to the solution of problems and political challenges, scientists and technicians associated with the resource and the forest industry and the country&#39;s environment and provide scientific and technical basis of production chains linked forestry program, prioritizing the development of forestry and the development of new options for diversification of forest products and services.</span></p>', 'CU', '8'),
(352, 842, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Agricultural Research Institute (ARI) is a Department under the Ministry of Agriculture, Natural Resources and Environment, of the Republic of Cyprus. The ARI was founded in 1962, after the independence of Cyprus, in cooperation with the Special Development Fund of the United Nations and the Food and Agriculture and became the property of the Government of Cyprus in 1967. The Institute conducts research directly applicable to the broad area of ​​agriculture and livestock in order to solve problems faced by Cypriot farmers. It evaluates new scientific and technological methods and suggests new procedures aimed at utilization of natural resources and improvement of animal and plant production. The main sectors and specialization in agriculture and livestock coexist under one roof, ensuring close cooperation between scientists and the rational use of equipment and other means.</span></p>', 'CY', '1'),
(354, 844, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The CEDAF is a foundation that promotes sustainable development of the agricultural and forestry sector, through training, information, institutional innovation and policy analysis and sector strategies, backed by an image of institutional excellence and high credibility in order to stimulate competitive agriculture that contributes to reducing poverty and protecting the environment.</span></p>', 'DO', '1'),
(355, 845, '', 'EC', '1'),
(356, 846, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The National Autonomous Agricultural Research Institute is a public entity, decentralized, which has legal personality and administrative, economic, financial and technical autonomy, with its own assets and special budget, linked to the Ministry of Agriculture.</span></p>', 'UY', '0'),
(357, 847, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">EDICA major mandate is to establish Egypt&rsquo;s National Agricultural Scientific Memory and support the Government Agricultural Development plans, by disseminating knowledge on agricultural research and transfer of modern agricultural technologies to user communities at universities, scientific research institutes and Agricultural Scientific Societies in Egypt and abroad. &nbsp;</span></p>', 'EG', '0'),
(358, 848, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Ethiopian Institute of Agricultural Reasearch (EIAR) has evolved through several stages since its first initiation during the late 1940s, following the establishment of agricultural and technical school of Ambo and Jimma.until the mid 1960&#39;s the Imperial College of Agricultural and Mechanical Arts&mdash;now Haramaya University&mdash;with its Agricultural Experiment Station at Debre Zeit&mdash;now Debre Zeit Research Center&mdash;was the major research entity. The establishment of the Institute of Agricultural Research (IAR) in 1966 saw the first nationally coordinated agricultural research system in Ethiopia. The EARS consist of EIAR, Regional Agricultural Research Institutes (RARIs), and Higher Learning Institutions (HLIs). EIAR is responsible for the running of federal research centers, and RARIs are administered by the regional state governments. In addition to conducting research at its federal centers, EIAR is charged with the responsibility for providing the overall coordination of agricultural research countrywide, and advising Government on agricultural research policy formulation. Currently, the EARS comprise 55 research centers and sites located across various agro-ecological zones. The research centers vary in their experience, human, facility, and other resources capacities. Some of the research centers and sites have one or more sub-centers and testing sites. &nbsp;</span></p>', 'ET', '0'),
(359, 849, '<p>Viikki Campus Library&#39;s primary target groups are students and staff on Viikki campus. Library&#39;s services are available for everyone who needs information in library&#39;s subject areas. The library focuses on the following subject areas: Ecology and environmental sciences Food sciences and nutrition Veterinary medicine Pharmacy Agricultural sciences Forest sciences Molecular biosciences Economics and social sciences</p>', 'FI', '0'),
(360, 850, '', 'GE', '0'),
(361, 851, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The CSIR is to become the force for accelerated social and economic development of Ghana through examining, exploring and creating Science and Technology catalysts<br />\r\nfor public and private wealth creation.</span></p>', 'GH', '0'),
(362, 852, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The establishment in Greece of the Mediterranean Agronomic Institute of Chania (MAICh which is accredited as CIHEAM Institute was ratified by Greece by 1537/85 (Official Journal A 48) and thus obtained the supralegislative validity of Article 28 par. 1 of the Greek Constitution. MAICh organises international, interdisciplinary post graduate programs and offers scholarships to an average of 150 candidates from 18 different countries annually. &nbsp;</span></p>', 'QC', '2'),
(363, 853, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The NAL is a specialised, scientific, public institution carrying national tasks, it is a budgetary institution. Its high authority is the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development. The library would like to attend enquirers working in agriculture from Hungary and abroad &ndash; students, lecturers, researchers, practical agrarians, enterpreneurs, primary producers etc. It is the most important collection of special literature in the Hungarian agricultural sector, furthermore, it is the co-ordination centre for libraries of institutions of higher agricultural education and for agricultural special libraries. The library is the agri-cultural centre of Middle- and East-Europe. NAL functions as deposit library of the FAO (Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations) and as such collects, processes, stores, and provides its publications. As Hungarian Agris-Centre takes part in building of the Agris database of FAO.</span></p>', 'HU', '0'),
(364, 854, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">The Indian Council of Agricultural Research (ICAR) is an autonomous organisation under the Department of Agricultural Research and Education (DARE), Ministry of Agriculture, Government of India.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;Formerly known as Imperial Council of Agricultural Research, it was established on 16 July 1929 as a registered society under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 in pursuance of the report of the Royal Commission on Agriculture. The ICAR has its headquarters at New Delhi. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'IN', '0'),
(365, 855, '<p>CIFOR advances human wellbeing, environmental conservation and equity by conducting research to inform policies and practices that affect forests in developing countries. CIFOR is a CGIAR Consortium Research Center. CIFOR&rsquo;s headquarters are in Bogor, Indonesia and it also has offices in Asia, Africa and South America.</p>', 'Q1', '0'),
(366, 856, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The main mission of the Agricultural Scientific Information &amp; Documentation Center(ASIDC) is about providing needed information for agricultural researchers</span></p>', 'IR', '0'),
(367, 857, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The GFAR document repository is a database of GFAR publications with access to the full-text digital document. The repository is the result of collaboration between the Global Forum&rsquo;s Secretariat and FAO&rsquo;s Library and Documentation Systems Division (WAICENT), who kindly provided a customized version of their Electronic Information Management System (EIMS). It is database driven and it interfaces with the web through XML. The main functionalities of the system are: Documents can be published and made visible on the web world wide Metadata records are managed in the system following information management standards (i.e. AGRIS AP metadata model) and terminology standards (i.e. AGROVOC) Electronic documents are saved and preserved in a file server The search can be customized according to different needs and can be performed using a RESTful web service.</span></p>', 'XR', '2'),
(368, 858, '<p>The Pollination Information Management System, (PIMS) is being developed through a collaboration between FAO and a number of national level organizations concerned with the conservation and sustainable use of pollination services for sustainable agriculture. The PIMS serves to organize and deliver accurate information on managing pollination services of key crops, globally, to farmers, farm advisors and land managers.</p>', 'XE', '2'),
(369, 859, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">EFSA&rsquo;s grants and procurement schemes play an important role in promoting cooperation within the EU scientific community. The initiative, which is highlighted in a new video, allows EFSA to tap into expertise from across Europe. It also provides eligible organisations with the opportunity to contribute to EFSA&rsquo;s work, access research funding and network with potential partners. EFSA has recently published a list of projects that it plans to launch by mid-2014 under its grants and procurement schemes.</span></p>', 'XE', '1'),
(370, 860, '<p>The library was established in Rome at the 1952 FAO Conference, according to the decisions of the 1950 Conference. It was named David Lubin Memorial Library by the Conference to honour the founder of the International Institute of Agriculture (IIA). The extensive IIA collection formed a solid base for the present-day Library, which is considered one of the world&#39;s finest collections in food, agriculture and international development.</p>', 'XF', '0'),
(371, 861, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Bioversity International is a recognized leader in agricultural biodiversity research working with more than 700 partners around the world to improve the lives of smallholder farmers and rural communities.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Bioversity International is a member of the CGIAR Consortium and a partner with Rome-based food and agriculture agencies Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN (FAO), International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD) and World Food Programme (WFP).&nbsp;</div>', 'QJ', '0'),
(372, 862, '', 'JP', '0'),
(373, 863, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The establishment of NCARTT goes back to the last 50&#39;s when the Department of Research and Extension was created. In the mid 80&rsquo;s, reformulated to become &ldquo;The National center for Agricultural Research and Technology Transfer&rdquo;. It was in charge of conducting applied Research at the national level.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;A few years later (1993) NCARTT became a semi-antonymous institution with administrative and financial independence. &nbsp; NCARTT has good relationships with many regional and international institution, such as the world bank, the European Commission, United Nations Development Project, FAO, USAID, German Technical Corporation (GTZ), International Development and Research Center (IDRC), ICARDA, ACSAD, AARINNA, Arab Fund For Economic and Social Development (AFESD), Arab Organization for Agricultural Development, and many others. &nbsp; NCARTT consists of a main headquarter located at&nbsp;Al-Hussein Agricultural Experiment Station at Balqa&#39;a and&nbsp;six Regional Centers in Deir Alla, Ramtha, Khaldieh, Mushaqar, Rabba, Shoubak.</div>', 'JO', '0'),
(374, 864, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">SWALIM stands for Somalia Water and Land Information Management, and the name says it all; it is an information management unit serving Somali administrations, non-governmental organisations, development agencies and UN organisations engaged in assisting Somali communities whose lives depend directly on water and land resources.One and a half decad</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">es of civil strife in Somalia have resulted in the loss or damage of most of the water- and land-related information collected in the previous half century. By producing baseline information, assessing natural resources, searching for existing information sources around the world, SWALIM is recovering as much of lost data as possible. The project is also re-establishing data collection networks in collaboration with partner agencies, to facilitate better assessment of rainfall, river flow, groundwater resources, land characteristics, degradation and land suitability as well as improving flood warning and flood management.&nbsp;</div>', 'SO', '1'),
(375, 865, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">he Kenya Agricultural Research Institute (KARI) is a premier national institution bringing together research programmes in food crops, horticultural and industrial crops, livestock and range management, land and water management, and socio-economics.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;KARI promotes sound agricultural research, technology generation and dissemination to ensure food security through improved productivity and environmental conservation.</p>\r\n</div>', 'KE', '2'),
(376, 866, '<p>The Fundamental library of the Latvia University of Agriculture is the largest agricultural library in Latvia. It is the National Centre of AGRIS/CARIS systems of the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations and the FAO Depository Library.</p>', 'LV', '0'),
(377, 867, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The WorldFish Center, a member of the CGIAR Consortium, is an international, nonprofit research organization. CGIAR is a global partnership that unites organizations engaged in research for a food secure future.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;CGIAR research is dedicated to reducing rural poverty, increasing food security, improving human health and nutrition, and ensuring more sustainable management of natural resources. It is carried out by the 15 centers who are members of the CGIAR Consortium in close collaboration with hundreds of partner organizations, including national and regional research institutes, civil society organizations, academia, and the private sector.</div>', 'QW', '0'),
(378, 868, '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">The Library currently holds a collection of 670,000 volumes of books and bound journals, as well as a collection of maps, sound recordings, microforms, video tapes and slides. The Library also subscribes to 80 online databases which provide access to about 80,000 full text articles on various fields and are accessible from and within and outside UPM through Website.</span></p>', 'MY', '0'),
(379, 869, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The CENIDA is the National Center for Agricultural Information and Documentation and aims to contribute to the scientific and technical development of the country agricultural sector through the identification, selection and collection of information on agricultural sciences and related to their respective processing and dissemination development.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'NI', '0'),
(380, 870, '', 'NO', '0'),
(381, 871, '<p>National Agricultural Research Centre (NARC), Islamabad established in 1984, is the largest research centre of the Pakistan Agricultural Research Council (PARC). NARC, with a total land area of approximately 1400 acres, is located near Rawal Lake, six kilometers south-east of Islamabad. Physical facilities in term of experimental fields, laboratories, green houses, gene bank, library/ documentation, auditorium, machinery &amp; lab equipment repair workshops, stores, hostels, cafeteria, audio visual studios, are also available at NARC.</p>', 'PK', '0'),
(382, 872, '<p>The International Potato Center, known by its Spanish acronym CIP, was founded in 1971 as a root and tuber research-for-development institution to deliver sustainable solutions to the pressing world problems of hunger, poverty, and the degradation of natural resources. CIP is truly a global center, with headquarters in Lima, Peru and offices in 30 countries across Asia, Africa, and Latin America. Working closely with hundreds of partners worldwide, CIP seeks to achieve food security, increased well-being, and gender equity for poor people in root and tuber farming, and food systems in the developing world. CIP furthers its mission through rigorous research, innovation in science and technology, and capacity strengthening among farmers and partners. CIP and its partners work across the agricultural spectrum. From the laboratory to the marketplace, CIP biologists, entomologists, agronomists, nutritionists, and social scientists conduct research and carry out projects.</p>', 'QP', '0'),
(383, 873, '<p>The National Agricultural Library is the main information center in the area of ​​agricultural sciences and related National Agrarian University - La Molina. It is regarded as the leading Agricultural Library Country and from January 2000 further develops the responsibility of &#39;Cross National System Coordinator documentation of Latin America and the Caribbean - SIDALC&#39;, assigned by the Inter-American Institute for Cooperation on Agriculture - IICA , in order to form the Network of Agricultural Libraries Peru-REBIAPE</p>', 'PE', '0'),
(384, 874, '', 'PE', '1'),
(385, 875, '', 'PH', 'M'),
(386, 876, '', 'PH', 'S'),
(387, 877, '<div class="group-header" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden" style="margin: 5px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit;">\r\n<div class="field-items" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit;">\r\n<div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded dc:description doap:description" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 5px !important; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit;">The Central Luzon State University shall develop socially responsible and empowered human resources and knowledge for poverty alleviation, environmental protection and global competitiveness towards sustainable development. &nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'PH', 'C'),
(388, 878, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Philippine Rice Research Institute (PhilRice) is a government corporate entity attached to the Department of Agriculture created through Executive Order 1061 on 5 November 1985 (as amended) to help develop high-yielding and cost-reducing technologies so farmers can produce enough rice for all Filipinos.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;The Institute accomplishes this mission through research and development work in our central and six branch stations, coordinating with a network that comprises 57 agencies and 70 seed centers strategically located nationwide. As proof the Institute&rsquo;s quality of service, PhilRice received the following certifications: ISO 9001:2008 (Quality Management), ISO 14001:2004 (Environmental Management), and OHSAS 18001:2007 (Occupational Health and Safety Assessment Series).&nbsp;</div>', 'PH', 'J'),
(389, 879, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">At present the VSU System has 10 colleges, three institutes and one school.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;These are the College of Agriculture, College of Forestry, College of Veterinary Medicine, College of Engineering and Agri-Industries, College of Arts and Sciences, College of Education, College of Fisheries (VSU-Tolosa Campus), College of Agri-Industrial Technology (VSU-Isabel Campus), College of Environmental and Agricultural Technology (VSU-Alangalang Campus), College of Education and Agricultural Technology (VSU-Villaba Campus), Institute of Human Kinetics, Institute of Tropical Ecology, Institute for Strategic Research and Development Studies, and the Graduate School. It also has an Open University which takes care of the distance education program.&nbsp;</div>', 'PH', 'V'),
(390, 880, '', 'PH', '0'),
(391, 881, '<p>CBR is a scientific library subordinated to the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development. It has branch in Pulawy. CBR collections - thematically restricted to agriculture, food processing industry and related sciences</p>', 'PL', '0'),
(392, 882, '', 'PT', '0'),
(393, 883, '<p>A Laboratory of Experimentation Research Institution and Provincial Rural Development Administration owns 70,000 of an Independent Volume and Periodical Publication. They provide literature information service through out Local Catss Library Official program which input upper information by internet.</p>', 'KR', '0'),
(394, 884, '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">The State Agrarian University of Moldova (SAUM), the only higher agricultural education institution in the Republic of Moldova in 1995 becomes a member of European University Association. &nbsp;</span></p>', 'MD', '1'),
(395, 885, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The objective of ICPA is to generate knowledge on soil, fertilisers and plant nutrition, and to develop technologies and skills to apply that knowledge. The results of public-funded research are normally published as scientific papers. Contract work is reported confidentially to customers, but this may also be published later on agreed terms.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Other important outputs include the development of technologies, such as modeling software packages, some of which lead to patents and commercially exploitable products. Advice on policy to Government and Parliamentary Commissions is other facet of ICPA outputs. ICPA develops research and service activities for public sector (ministries, county agencies, Universities, NGOs) and private sector (small and medium companies, farms, industrial units), not only from Romania, but also from other countries. The outputs are generated and provided using the most advanced technology, including friendly visualisation (e.g. dynamic maps on monitor, required maps on plotter) and interactive scenarios based on models integrated in GIS, expert systems and decision support systems. ICPA Computing Centre provides agricultural/environment information services - as the Romanian AGRIS/CARIS Centre in the FAO&#39;s AGRIS/CARIS network. &nbsp;</div>', 'RO', '0'),
(396, 886, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">he scientific journal &ldquo;Resources and Technology&rdquo; is an interdisciplinary peer-reviewed online journal, has an open access publication model, and is published two times a year by Petrozavodsk State University in Russian and English.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;&ldquo;Resources and Technology&rdquo; is a follow-up of &rdquo;Research Reports of Forest Engineering Faculty of Petrozavodsk State University&rdquo;, which were published in 1996-2012. The journal continues to publish articles in various fields of the forest sector (forest policy and economics, the various aspects of sustainable forest management, wood harvesting, forest industry, forest bioenergy, wooden construction, and forestry machinery) and extends the scope welcoming submissions from interdisciplinary studies on natural resources management and related technology. &nbsp; The journal publishes analytical overviews, original research and brief communications. The aim is to encourage scientists to publish their research in as much detail as possible. There is no page limit. In addition, unique features of this journal are i) manuscripts regarding interdisciplinary studies on renewable natural resources in the former Soviet and Nordic countries will be particularly welcomed; ii) manuscripts communicating to a broader audience with regard to projects financed from public funds will be accepted. Special issues are an effective way to draw attention to the on-going research and developing projects. &ldquo;Resources and Technology&rdquo; aims to publish special issues that focus on topics of interest to the journal&#39;s readers. &nbsp; &ldquo;Resources and Technology&rdquo; applies a double-blind peer review process, in which all manuscripts will be reviewed by at least two reviewers. The publication is free of charge. This is an open access journal which means that all content is freely available without charge to the user. It is allowed to read, download, copy, distribute, print, search, or link to the full texts of the articles in this journal without asking prior permission from the publisher or the author. Plagiarism checker applied to all submitted manuscripts. The&nbsp;journal allows authors to retain copyright in their article with no restrictions.&nbsp;Authors can post the final, peer-reviewed manuscript version to any repository or website.</p>\r\n</div>', 'RU', '4'),
(397, 887, '', 'RU', '0'),
(398, 888, '<p>The Journal of Stress Physiology &amp; Biochemistry publishes experimental articles, reviews, methods and hypotheses that deal with physiological and biochemichal reactions of plant and animal organisms to abiotic and biotic stress factors. Papers should be intelligible to as wide an audience as possible; particular attention should be paid to the Introduction and Discussion sections, which should clearly draw attention to the novelty and significance of the data reported.</p>', 'RU', '1'),
(399, 889, '', 'RU', '2'),
(400, 890, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Matica Srpska Library in its funds has more than 3,500,000 books and other publications. The Library receives the sample copy of all the publications of Serbia.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;The Library has 671 old manuscript books, the greatest collection of Serbian books from the 15th to the 19th century and the richest collection of Serbian periodicals from the 18th and the first half of the 19th century. The legacies and the donated libraries both of individuals and institutions are preserved as the special collections. The Library exchanges publications with 320 foreign libraries and institutions. Cataloguing and bibliography work are automated since 1989. CIP cataloging is made for all Vojvodina publications. In August 20011, the Library data base has had over 1.170.000 entries. The Library gives services in research domestic as well as foreign data bases. In its 7 reading-rooms there are 250 seats. The Library is constantly expanding its publishing and exhibit work. Restoration and conservation is done in a modern well equipped laboratory. As the central library for all University and public libraries in Vojvodina organizes expert exams for all Vojvodina libraries.&nbsp;</div>', 'RS', '0'),
(401, 891, '', 'SK', '0'),
(402, 892, '', 'SK', '1'),
(403, 893, '<p>The Slovak Library of Forestry and Wood Sciences at the Technical University in Zvolen is an academic library of the Technical University in Zvolen and fulfils also the function of the only specialised scientific library in the fields of forestry and wood sciences within the Slovak Republic. A main role of the Library is to collect, process, store and make accessible scientific and technical literature and information for the Technical University pedagogical and research workers, students, as well as for other professionals and institutions in the Slovak Republic and abroad. The Library provides free access to information on all types of media, helps to satisfy cultural, information, scientific, research and educational needs, supports life-long learning and intellectual growth.</p>', 'SK', '2'),
(404, 894, '', 'SI', '0'),
(405, 895, '', 'AJ', '0'),
(406, 896, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The National Institute for Agricultural and Food Research and Technology (INIA) is an autonomous Public Research Organisation (OPI) of the State Secretariat of Research, Development and Innovation of the Ministry of Economy and Competitiveness.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;It&#39;s the only public research organisation of the National State Administration exclusively dedicated to agrifood and forestry research. INIA&#39;s mission, in coordination with the equivalent institutions of the Autonomous Regions is to contribute to continuous and sustainable progress through development of environmentally friendly technologies. Its priority objectives are to satisfy the new research demands on agricultural, livestock and forestry production, mitigate the effects of global change and contribute to food safety and the fight against hunger in line with the Objectives of the Millennium.&nbsp;</div>', 'ES', '0'),
(407, 897, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Spanish Journal of Rural Development (SJRD) es una revista de reciente creaci&oacute;n, publicada por la Asociaci&oacute;n Gallega de Investigadores para el Desarrollo Rural (AGAIDERU), que intenta ser un forum de discusi&oacute;n que contribuya a la mejora del conocimiento del mundo rural, centrado en su desarrollo sostenible.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Es una revista multidisciplinar en la que tienen cabida trabajos centrados en temas forestales, agron&oacute;micos, medioambientales, de planeamiento rural, de cooperaci&oacute;n internacional, socioecon&oacute;micos,., pero siempre enfocados en su aplicaci&oacute;n para lograr un Desarrollo Rural Sostenible de las poblaciones locales. &nbsp;</div>', 'ES', 'A'),
(408, 898, '<p>The Mediterranean Agronomic Institute of Zaragoza (IAMZ) is, since its accreditation in 1969, one of four Mediterranean Agronomic Institutes International Centre for Advanced Mediterranean Agronomic Studies (CIHEAM). IAMZ meets the objectives of development of agricultural cooperation CIHEAM fixed by updating and improving the training of professionals and promoting research programs of common interest for agriculture in the Mediterranean region.</p>', 'QC', '6'),
(409, 899, '', 'ES', '1'),
(410, 900, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">IWMI is one of 15 international research centers supported by the network of 60 governments, private foundations and international and regional organizations collectively known as the Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research (CGIAR).</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;It is a non-profit organization with a staff of 350 and offices in over 10 countries across Asia and Africa and Headquarters in Colombo, Sri Lanka.&nbsp;</div>', 'QL', '0'),
(411, 901, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">The vision of the ARC is to become a centre of excellence in agricultural research by developing skilled manpower and conducting quality research to generate technologies that would ensure sustainable crop production, and to play an active role in technology transfer process.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;The mission of the ARC is to plan, develop and implement research designed to produce technologies and systems that are required to ensure high and sustainable crop productivity, food security and export capacity. The ARC is entrusted with applied agricultural research on food and industrial crops, forestry, livestock and food technology, and with ecological and regional responsibilities to develop sustainable production systems in the Sudan. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'SD', '0'),
(412, 902, '', 'DJ', '0'),
(413, 903, '', 'CH', '1'),
(414, 904, '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">The research of Agroscope is aimed at providing safe and flavoursome food, a healthy environment and an innovative and competitive agriculture! Research into agriculture, nutrition and the environment is an investment in the foundations of our future. &nbsp;</span></p>', 'CH', '0'),
(415, 905, '', 'SY', '0'),
(416, 906, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">Thai National AGRIS Centre was established in March 13, 1980 by General National FAO Committee, Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives cooperated with Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; display: inline;">&nbsp;Collects information related to agricultural sciences and technologies produced/printed in Thailand including those of agricultural information about Thailand produced/printed in abroad Technical management of agricultural information system: indexing, cataloging, creating Thai Agricultural Database Care and preservation of valuable agricultural information materials in form of microfich and electronic forms (including unpublished documents considered valuable is also preserved) Agricultural information services and organize activities in promoting to make the most use of collected information in databases Conduct research project in order to develop information service strategies Organize activities to develop agricultural information system Co-operate with other organizations in developing agricultural information system and being national representative in co- operating with AGRIS Coordinating Centres at regional and international levels &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'TH', '0'),
(417, 907, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The INRGREF deals with research on the Rural Engineering, Water and Forests: The research interests include control, the economy and the promotion of the use of water for irrigation of crops, problems soil salinity, sewage, agricultural machinery, ETUC, reforestation, improved timber and livestock production, conservation of natural resources, use and management of forests and rangelands and energy new and renewable.</div>', 'TN', '1'),
(418, 908, '', 'TR', '0'),
(419, 909, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Ukrainian Institute for Scientific, Technical and Economic Information (UkrISTEI) is the main Ukraine research institute for the questions of scientific, technical and economic information.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;Efforts of UkrISTEI team are directed at creation of the forming system for national information resources on scientific, technical and innovation activity, accessibility to them, information and analytical providing of all levels users.</div>', 'UA', '0'),
(420, 910, '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 15.3600006103516px;">Eldis is an online information service providing free access to relevant, up-to-date and diverse research on international development issues. The database includes over&nbsp;</span><a a="" href="http://www.eldis.org/go/what-s-new" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(78, 78, 78); font-size: 13px; line-height: 15.3600006103516px;">40,000 summaries</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 15.3600006103516px;">&nbsp;and provides free links to full-text research and policy documents from over 8,000 publishers. Each document is selected by members of our editorial team. The&nbsp;website is predominantly used by development practitioners, decision makers and researchers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'GB', '2'),
(421, 911, '', 'US', '4'),
(422, 912, '', 'US', '3'),
(423, 913, '<p>AgEcon Search is a free, open access repository of full-text scholarly literature in agricultural and applied economics.</p>', 'US', '2'),
(424, 914, '&nbsp;', 'UY', '0'),
