(509, 1112, '<p>The Centre for Information and Documentation Scientific and Technical Public Institution has industrial and commercial (EPIC ), established by Decree No. 87-145 of 5 May 1987 , as amended by Decree No. 92-661 of 8 July 1992, CIDST is under the dual supervision of the Ministry of National Education and Scientific Research and the Ministry of Finance and Budget. CIDST missions are to : - Contribute to the development and implementation of national policy research on information, communication and dissemination of knowledge; - Support development actors through better information flow in general and the dissemination of scientific and technical information on the results of national and international research; - Provide scientific expertise matter authentication and information security ; - Provide training courses for better information management and capacity building professionals.</p>', 'MG', '0'),
(510, 1115, '<div class="expanding-formatter-summary" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Chitedze Agricultural Research Station (CARS) was established in the 1948 to expand the work which was being carried out at Likuni Experiment Station.This was done under the leadership of Mr. S. Hoyle, the first Chief Agricultural Research Officer (director) in Malawi.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="expanding-formatter-content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px; display: inline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;The first field experiments on the station were conducted in the 1949/50 season. Since the inception of the station several institutions have been established within the premises. Colby College of Agriculture, which later moved and was renamed the Natural Resources College, was opened in 1956. The Grain Legumes Research Unit (GLRU) was established in 1964 under the auspices of the Agricultural Research Council of Central Africa. The GLRU was in 1975 handed over to the Department of Agricultural Research.</div>', 'MW', '0'),
