(145, 1002, '<p>The Institute of Agricultural Research, INIA , is the principal agricultural research institution in Chile , being a private corporation , non-profit organization under the Ministry of Agriculture. It was created in 1964 by the Institute of Agricultural Development Corporation Production Development , University of Chile, the Pontificia Universidad Cat&oacute;lica de Chile and the Universidad de Concepci&oacute;n. It has a national coverage , which is composed of 11 Regional Research Centers ( CRI), located in the regions of Coquimbo, Valparaiso , Metropolitana, Libertador Bernardo O&#39;Higgins, Maule , Bio Bio , La Araucania , Los Lagos, the General Carlos Ib&aacute;&ntilde;ez del Campo and Magallanes. From the CRI depend Experimental Centres and Technical Offices . INIA &#39;s mission is &#39; Building and transfer knowledge and global strategic technologies for producing innovation and improve competitiveness in agriculture and forestry .</p>'),
