(171, 1071, '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Ubuntu, Arial, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">Teagasc is the agriculture and food development authority in Ireland. Its mission is to support science-based innovation in the agri-food sector and the broader bioeconomy that will underpin profitability, competitiveness and sustainability. &nbsp;</span></p>'),
(172, 1075, '<p>ISMEA (Institute of Agricultural and Food Services Market) is a public body established by the economic unification of the Institute for Studies, Research and Information on Agricultural Market (formerly ISMEA) and the Fund for the Education of Peasant Property, with October 29, 1999 legislative Decree n. 419, on the &#39;reorganization of the system of national public bodies&#39;.</p>'),
